                    <comment id="13162806" author="c_koell" created="Mon, 5 Dec 2011 14:30:19 +0000"  >+1 from me :-)</comment>
                    <comment id="13162807" author="jukkaz" created="Mon, 5 Dec 2011 14:39:22 +0000"  >Done in revision 1210476.</comment>
                    <comment id="13163107" author="fmeschbe" created="Mon, 5 Dec 2011 22:25:58 +0000"  >Sorry for being late. But I don&amp;#39;t think, that I really like this ...&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
If you want to integrate this you can have an Maven Eclipse plugin setup to have the JavaCC process run on demand. Checking in generated code as primary source does not feel right.</comment>
                    <comment id="13163429" author="tmueller" created="Tue, 6 Dec 2011 08:24:19 +0000"  >In this case, checking in the generated code probably simplifies a lot (anyway I hope we don&amp;#39;t need JavaCC in the future).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Felix, do you have a list of concrete disadvantages? If not that&amp;#39;s OK.</comment>
                    <comment id="13163517" author="jukkaz" created="Tue, 6 Dec 2011 10:46:04 +0000"  >So far I haven&amp;#39;t figured out a way to make Eclipse and other IDEs pick up the generated sources automatically during an import. Until we have such a patch I think having the precompiled sources in svn under src/main/java is the best solution here.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
PS. For future reference: When changing the JavaCC sources, use &amp;quot;mvn clean install -Pjavacc&amp;quot; in jackrabbit-spi-commons and commit the updated files.</comment>
                    <comment id="13163529" author="mduerig" created="Tue, 6 Dec 2011 11:24:36 +0000"  >&amp;gt; PS. For future reference: When changing the JavaCC sources, use &amp;quot;mvn clean install -Pjavacc&amp;quot; in jackrabbit-spi-commons and commit the updated files. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I&amp;#39;m almost sure this will backfire since people will forget about this. At the very least we should put this note into the headers of all the JavaCC source files. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
However, is it really worth to trade correctness for convenience here? I feel the IDE pain too. In fact I felt it for the past couple of years. Why the sudden hurry now?</comment>
